{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BLBSwtArvA1VyeF2gJs9ro","type":"tool_result","content":"     1‚Üí# Host Workflow Design (`host.cloche`)\n     2‚Üí\n     3‚Üí**Date:** 2026-03-06\n     4‚Üí**Status:** Design\n     5‚Üí\n     6‚Üí## Problem\n     7‚Üí\n     8‚ÜíThe orchestrator's intake ‚Üí process ‚Üí output loop is hard-coded in Go\n     9‚Üí(`internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go`). Every project must follow the same flow:\n    10‚Üípull task ‚Üí generate prompt ‚Üí dispatch `develop` container run. This can't be changed\n    11‚Üíwithout modifying Cloche itself. Projects that need different orchestration strategies\n    12‚Üí(push to GitHub for review, group tickets into feature branches, stacked commits, etc.)\n    13‚Üíhave no extension point.\n    14‚Üí\n    15‚Üí## Solution: `host.cloche`\n    16‚Üí\n    17‚ÜíA special workflow file at `.cloche/host.cloche`. It uses the same DSL as container\n    18‚Üíworkflow files, with one additional step type (`workflow`). Steps in this file execute\n    19‚Üíon the **host machine**, not inside a container.\n    20‚Üí\n    21‚ÜíThe workflow named `main` in this file becomes the per-task orchestration loop\n    22‚Üífor that project. The Go daemon becomes the executor of this workflow rather than the\n    23‚Üíhard-coded logic holder.\n    24‚Üí\n    25‚Üí### File location\n    26‚Üí\n    27‚Üí```\n    28‚Üí.cloche/host.cloche\n    29‚Üí```\n    30‚Üí\n    31‚ÜíIf the file does not exist, the daemon falls back to the current hard-coded behavior\n    32‚Üí(pull task ‚Üí LLM prompt generation ‚Üí dispatch container workflow).\n    33‚Üí\n    34‚Üí---\n    35‚Üí\n    36‚Üí## DSL additions\n    37‚Üí\n    38‚Üí### New step type: `workflow`\n    39‚Üí\n    40‚ÜíA step with `workflow_name` config key is a workflow-dispatch step. It dispatches a\n    41‚Üínamed container workflow run and blocks until that run completes.\n    42‚Üí\n    43‚Üí```\n    44‚Üístep develop {\n    45‚Üí  workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    46‚Üí  results = [success, fail]\n    47‚Üí}\n    48‚Üí```\n    49‚Üí\n    50‚Üí`workflow_name` is added to `knownStepConfigKeys` in `domain/workflow.go`.\n    51‚Üí\n    52‚Üí`StepTypeWorkflow` is added to the `StepType` enum in `domain/workflow.go`.\n    53‚Üí\n    54‚ÜíThe parser (`dsl/parser.go`) infers `StepTypeWorkflow` when `workflow_name` is present\n    55‚Üí(same pattern as `run` ‚Üí script, `prompt` ‚Üí agent).\n    56‚Üí\n    57‚Üí### Prompt input for `workflow` steps\n    58‚Üí\n    59‚ÜíThe container workflow needs a prompt. By convention, a `workflow` step reads the\n    60‚Üíprevious step's captured output file as the prompt. This is the primary data-passing\n    61‚Üímechanism.\n    62‚Üí\n    63‚ÜíAn optional config key `prompt_step` overrides which step's output to read:\n    64‚Üí```\n    65‚Üístep develop {\n    66‚Üí  workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    67‚Üí  prompt_step   = \"prepare-prompt\"\n    68‚Üí  results       = [success, fail]\n    69‚Üí}\n    70‚Üí```\n    71‚Üí\n    72‚Üí---\n    73‚Üí\n    74‚Üí## Step output capture\n    75‚Üí\n    76‚ÜíEvery step in a host workflow execution writes its output (stdout of `run` steps,\n    77‚Üífinal response of `prompt` steps) to a file:\n    78‚Üí\n    79‚Üí```\n    80‚Üí.cloche/<orch-run-id>/main/<step_name>.out\n    81‚Üí```\n    82‚Üí\n    83‚Üí`<orch-run-id>` is a unique ID for this orchestration invocation, formatted the same\n    84‚Üíway as workflow run IDs (e.g. `main-bold-hawk`).\n    85‚Üí\n    86‚ÜíThe daemon tracks the most recently completed step's output path and passes it to the\n    87‚Üínext step as `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`.\n    88‚Üí\n    89‚Üí---\n    90‚Üí\n    91‚Üí## Environment variables injected into host steps\n    92‚Üí\n    93‚ÜíAll `run` and `prompt` steps receive:\n    94‚Üí\n    95‚Üí| Variable | Value |\n    96‚Üí|----------|-------|\n    97‚Üí| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Task ID being processed |\n    98‚Üí| `CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE` | Task summary/title |\n    99‚Üí| `CLOCHE_TASK_BODY` | Task full body/description |\n   100‚Üí| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory |\n   101‚Üí| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output |\n   102‚Üí| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the previous step's output file |\n   103‚Üí\n   104‚ÜíFor `workflow` steps, `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` is read automatically (unless `prompt_step`\n   105‚Üíoverrides it).\n   106‚Üí\n   107‚Üí---\n   108‚Üí\n   109‚Üí## Executor: `internal/orchestrator/hostrunner.go`\n   110‚Üí\n   111‚ÜíNew file. Implements the host workflow execution loop.\n   112‚Üí\n   113‚Üí```go\n   114‚Üítype HostRunner struct {\n   115‚Üí    Dispatch  RunDispatcher      // existing: dispatches a container workflow run\n   116‚Üí    WaitRun   RunWaiter          // new: blocks until a run ID completes, returns final state\n   117‚Üí    AgentCmd  string             // command to invoke for prompt steps on host\n   118‚Üí}\n   119‚Üí\n   120‚Üí// RunWorkflow executes the named workflow from a parsed host.cloche Workflow\n   121‚Üí// for a single task. Returns the final result (\"done\" or \"abort\").\n   122‚Üífunc (r *HostRunner) RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow, task ports.Task, orchRunID string) (string, error)\n   123‚Üí```\n   124‚Üí\n   125‚ÜíStep execution:\n   126‚Üí\n   127‚Üí- **`script` step** (`run` key): `exec.Command` with env vars, stdout captured to\n   128‚Üí  `<step>.out`, stderr to `<step>.err`. Exit 0 ‚Üí `success`, non-zero ‚Üí `fail`.\n   129‚Üí- **`agent` step** (`prompt` key): invoke `AgentCmd` on host with the prompt file\n   130‚Üí  contents injected. Capture output. Exit 0 ‚Üí `success`, non-zero ‚Üí `fail`.\n   131‚Üí- **`workflow` step** (`workflow_name` key): read prompt from prev step's `.out` file\n   132‚Üí  (or `prompt_step` override), call `Dispatch`, then call `WaitRun` to block until\n   133‚Üí  the container run completes. Map `succeeded` ‚Üí `success`, `failed`/`cancelled` ‚Üí\n   134‚Üí  `fail`.\n   135‚Üí\n   136‚Üí`WaitRun` is a new port interface:\n   137‚Üí\n   138‚Üí```go\n   139‚Üí// RunWaiter blocks until the run with the given ID reaches a terminal state.\n   140‚Üítype RunWaiter interface {\n   141‚Üí    WaitRun(ctx context.Context, runID string) (domain.RunState, error)\n   142‚Üí}\n   143‚Üí```\n   144‚Üí\n   145‚ÜíThe gRPC server / store already has `GetRun`; the waiter can poll it with backoff or\n   146‚Üísubscribe to the `OnRunComplete` event. A simple polling implementation (1s interval)\n   147‚Üíis sufficient initially.\n   148‚Üí\n   149‚Üí---\n   150‚Üí\n   151‚Üí## Refactored `orchestrator.Orchestrator`\n   152‚Üí\n   153‚Üí`Orchestrator.Run()` is updated:\n   154‚Üí\n   155‚Üí**Current flow (hardcoded):**\n   156‚Üí1. Pull ready tasks\n   157‚Üí2. Claim task\n   158‚Üí3. Call `promptGen.Generate(task)`\n   159‚Üí4. Call `dispatch(workflow, projectDir, prompt)` ‚Üí runID\n   160‚Üí5. (In-flight counter managed, `OnRunComplete` decrements it)\n   161‚Üí\n   162‚Üí**New flow (when `host.cloche` exists):**\n   163‚Üí1. Pull ready tasks\n   164‚Üí2. Claim task\n   165‚Üí3. Parse `.cloche/host.cloche` ‚Üí find `main` workflow\n   166‚Üí4. Generate an `orchRunID` (`main-<namegen>`)\n   167‚Üí5. Spin up a goroutine: call `hostRunner.RunWorkflow(ctx, orch wf, task, orchRunID)`\n   168‚Üí6. On goroutine return: decrement in-flight, update task state (success/fail)\n   169‚Üí\n   170‚ÜíThe old `promptGen` and `dispatch` are still used as the **fallback** when\n   171‚Üí`host.cloche` is absent (no breaking change for existing projects).\n   172‚Üí\n   173‚Üí`WaitRun` needs access to the run store. Wire it in `initOrchestrator` in\n   174‚Üí`cmd/cloched/main.go`.\n   175‚Üí\n   176‚Üí---\n   177‚Üí\n   178‚Üí## Default `host.cloche` (from `cloche init`)\n   179‚Üí\n   180‚Üí```\n   181‚Üí# host.cloche ‚Äî orchestration workflow (runs on host, not in container)\n   182‚Üí# Steps here execute as the daemon user. Keep operations simple and safe.\n   183‚Üí\n   184‚Üíworkflow \"main\" {\n   185‚Üí  step prepare-prompt {\n   186‚Üí    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n   187‚Üí    results = [success, fail]\n   188‚Üí  }\n   189‚Üí\n   190‚Üí  step develop {\n   191‚Üí    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n   192‚Üí    results       = [success, fail]\n   193‚Üí  }\n   194‚Üí\n   195‚Üí  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n   196‚Üí  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n   197‚Üí  develop:success        -> done\n   198‚Üí  develop:fail           -> done\n   199‚Üí}\n   200‚Üí```\n   201‚Üí\n   202‚ÜíAnd `.cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` (created by init, chmod +x):\n   203‚Üí\n   204‚Üí```bash\n   205‚Üí#!/usr/bin/env bash\n   206‚Üí# Default prompt generator. Uses task env vars injected by cloched.\n   207‚Üí# Write the prompt to $CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT (also echoed to stdout).\n   208‚Üíset -euo pipefail\n   209‚Üí\n   210‚Üíprompt=\"## Task: ${CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE}\n   211‚Üí\n   212‚Üí${CLOCHE_TASK_BODY}\"\n   213‚Üí\n   214‚Üíecho \"$prompt\"\n   215‚Üí[ -n \"${CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT:-}\" ] && echo \"$prompt\" > \"$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT\"\n   216‚Üí```\n   217‚Üí\n   218‚Üí---\n   219‚Üí\n   220‚Üí## `.gitignore` update\n   221‚Üí\n   222‚Üí`cloche init` adds `.cloche/scripts/` is NOT gitignored (scripts are project config).\n   223‚ÜíThe orchestration run output dirs follow the same pattern as container run dirs:\n   224‚Üí`.cloche/main-*/` is gitignored via the existing `.cloche/*/` rule.\n   225‚Üí\n   226‚Üí---\n   227‚Üí\n   228‚Üí## Safety notes\n   229‚Üí\n   230‚Üí- Host steps run with the same OS privileges as the `cloched` process.\n   231‚Üí- No network isolation.\n   232‚Üí- `host.cloche` should only reference scripts that are committed to the project.\n   233‚Üí- Document that `prompt` steps in `host.cloche` invoke an LLM agent with full host\n   234‚Üí  filesystem access ‚Äî use judiciously.\n   235‚Üí\n   236‚Üí---\n   237‚Üí\n   238‚Üí## Changes required\n   239‚Üí\n   240‚Üí| File | Change |\n   241‚Üí|------|--------|\n   242‚Üí| `internal/domain/workflow.go` | Add `StepTypeWorkflow`, add `workflow_name`/`prompt_step` to `knownStepConfigKeys` |\n   243‚Üí| `internal/dsl/parser.go` | Infer `StepTypeWorkflow` when `workflow_name` key is present |\n   244‚Üí| `internal/orchestrator/hostrunner.go` | New: host workflow executor |\n   245‚Üí| `internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go` | Refactor `Run()` to use `HostRunner` when `host.cloche` exists; fall back to current behavior otherwise |\n   246‚Üí| `internal/ports/container.go` | Add `RunWaiter` interface |\n   247‚Üí| `cmd/cloched/main.go` | Wire `HostRunner` into orchestrator init |\n   248‚Üí| `cmd/cloche/init.go` | Create `host.cloche` and `scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` |\n   249‚Üí"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9be06376-5a43-40f9-8380-030cf073c859","uuid":"0cec8a9f-f5b7-4183-a58f-ffd6dfd21369","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md","content":"# Host Workflow Design (`host.cloche`)\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-06\n**Status:** Design\n\n## Problem\n\nThe orchestrator's intake ‚Üí process ‚Üí output loop is hard-coded in Go\n(`internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go`). Every project must follow the same flow:\npull task ‚Üí generate prompt ‚Üí dispatch `develop` container run. This can't be changed\nwithout modifying Cloche itself. Projects that need different orchestration strategies\n(push to GitHub for review, group tickets into feature branches, stacked commits, etc.)\nhave no extension point.\n\n## Solution: `host.cloche`\n\nA special workflow file at `.cloche/host.cloche`. It uses the same DSL as container\nworkflow files, with one additional step type (`workflow`). Steps in this file execute\non the **host machine**, not inside a container.\n\nThe workflow named `main` in this file becomes the per-task orchestration loop\nfor that project. The Go daemon becomes the executor of this workflow rather than the\nhard-coded logic holder.\n\n### File location\n\n```\n.cloche/host.cloche\n```\n\nIf the file does not exist, the daemon falls back to the current hard-coded behavior\n(pull task ‚Üí LLM prompt generation ‚Üí dispatch container workflow).\n\n---\n\n## DSL additions\n\n### New step type: `workflow`\n\nA step with `workflow_name` config key is a workflow-dispatch step. It dispatches a\nnamed container workflow run and blocks until that run completes.\n\n```\nstep develop {\n  workflow_name = \"develop\"\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n`workflow_name` is added to `knownStepConfigKeys` in `domain/workflow.go`.\n\n`StepTypeWorkflow` is added to the `StepType` enum in `domain/workflow.go`.\n\nThe parser (`dsl/parser.go`) infers `StepTypeWorkflow` when `workflow_name` is present\n(same pattern as `run` ‚Üí script, `prompt` ‚Üí agent).\n\n### Prompt input for `workflow` steps\n\nThe container workflow needs a prompt. By convention, a `workflow` step reads the\nprevious step's captured output file as the prompt. This is the primary data-passing\nmechanism.\n\nAn optional config key `prompt_step` overrides which step's output to read:\n```\nstep develop {\n  workflow_name = \"develop\"\n  prompt_step   = \"prepare-prompt\"\n  results       = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step output capture\n\nEvery step in a host workflow execution writes its output (stdout of `run` steps,\nfinal response of `prompt` steps) to a file:\n\n```\n.cloche/<orch-run-id>/main/<step_name>.out\n```\n\n`<orch-run-id>` is a unique ID for this orchestration invocation, formatted the same\nway as workflow run IDs (e.g. `main-bold-hawk`).\n\nThe daemon tracks the most recently completed step's output path and passes it to the\nnext step as `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`.\n\n---\n\n## Environment variables injected into host steps\n\nAll `run` and `prompt` steps receive:\n\n| Variable | Value |\n|----------|-------|\n| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Task ID being processed |\n| `CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE` | Task summary/title |\n| `CLOCHE_TASK_BODY` | Task full body/description |\n| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory |\n| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output |\n| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the previous step's output file |\n\nFor `workflow` steps, `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` is read automatically (unless `prompt_step`\noverrides it).\n\n---\n\n## Executor: `internal/orchestrator/hostrunner.go`\n\nNew file. Implements the host workflow execution loop.\n\n```go\ntype HostRunner struct {\n    Dispatch  RunDispatcher      // existing: dispatches a container workflow run\n    WaitRun   RunWaiter          // new: blocks until a run ID completes, returns final state\n    AgentCmd  string             // command to invoke for prompt steps on host\n}\n\n// RunWorkflow executes the named workflow from a parsed host.cloche Workflow\n// for a single task. Returns the final result (\"done\" or \"abort\").\nfunc (r *HostRunner) RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow, task ports.Task, orchRunID string) (string, error)\n```\n\nStep execution:\n\n- **`script` step** (`run` key): `exec.Command` with env vars, stdout captured to\n  `<step>.out`, stderr to `<step>.err`. Exit 0 ‚Üí `success`, non-zero ‚Üí `fail`.\n- **`agent` step** (`prompt` key): invoke `AgentCmd` on host with the prompt file\n  contents injected. Capture output. Exit 0 ‚Üí `success`, non-zero ‚Üí `fail`.\n- **`workflow` step** (`workflow_name` key): read prompt from prev step's `.out` file\n  (or `prompt_step` override), call `Dispatch`, then call `WaitRun` to block until\n  the container run completes. Map `succeeded` ‚Üí `success`, `failed`/`cancelled` ‚Üí\n  `fail`.\n\n`WaitRun` is a new port interface:\n\n```go\n// RunWaiter blocks until the run with the given ID reaches a terminal state.\ntype RunWaiter interface {\n    WaitRun(ctx context.Context, runID string) (domain.RunState, error)\n}\n```\n\nThe gRPC server / store already has `GetRun`; the waiter can poll it with backoff or\nsubscribe to the `OnRunComplete` event. A simple polling implementation (1s interval)\nis sufficient initially.\n\n---\n\n## Refactored `orchestrator.Orchestrator`\n\n`Orchestrator.Run()` is updated:\n\n**Current flow (hardcoded):**\n1. Pull ready tasks\n2. Claim task\n3. Call `promptGen.Generate(task)`\n4. Call `dispatch(workflow, projectDir, prompt)` ‚Üí runID\n5. (In-flight counter managed, `OnRunComplete` decrements it)\n\n**New flow (when `host.cloche` exists):**\n1. Pull ready tasks\n2. Claim task\n3. Parse `.cloche/host.cloche` ‚Üí find `main` workflow\n4. Generate an `orchRunID` (`main-<namegen>`)\n5. Spin up a goroutine: call `hostRunner.RunWorkflow(ctx, orch wf, task, orchRunID)`\n6. On goroutine return: decrement in-flight, update task state (success/fail)\n\nThe old `promptGen` and `dispatch` are still used as the **fallback** when\n`host.cloche` is absent (no breaking change for existing projects).\n\n`WaitRun` needs access to the run store. Wire it in `initOrchestrator` in\n`cmd/cloched/main.go`.\n\n---\n\n## Default `host.cloche` (from `cloche init`)\n\n```\n# host.cloche ‚Äî orchestration workflow (runs on host, not in container)\n# Steps here execute as the daemon user. Keep operations simple and safe.\n\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results       = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n  develop:success        -> done\n  develop:fail           -> done\n}\n```\n\nAnd `.cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` (created by init, chmod +x):\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Default prompt generator. Uses task env vars injected by cloched.\n# Write the prompt to $CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT (also echoed to stdout).\nset -euo pipefail\n\nprompt=\"## Task: ${CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE}\n\n${CLOCHE_TASK_BODY}\"\n\necho \"$prompt\"\n[ -n \"${CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT:-}\" ] && echo \"$prompt\" > \"$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## `.gitignore` update\n\n`cloche init` adds `.cloche/scripts/` is NOT gitignored (scripts are project config).\nThe orchestration run output dirs follow the same pattern as container run dirs:\n`.cloche/main-*/` is gitignored via the existing `.cloche/*/` rule.\n\n---\n\n## Safety notes\n\n- Host steps run with the same OS privileges as the `cloched` process.\n- No network isolation.\n- `host.cloche` should only reference scripts that are committed to the project.\n- Document that `prompt` steps in `host.cloche` invoke an LLM agent with full host\n  filesystem access ‚Äî use judiciously.\n\n---\n\n## Changes required\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `internal/domain/workflow.go` | Add `StepTypeWorkflow`, add `workflow_name`/`prompt_step` to `knownStepConfigKeys` |\n| `internal/dsl/parser.go` | Infer `StepTypeWorkflow` when `workflow_name` key is present |\n| `internal/orchestrator/hostrunner.go` | New: host workflow executor |\n| `internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go` | Refactor `Run()` to use `HostRunner` when `host.cloche` exists; fall back to current behavior otherwise |\n| `internal/ports/container.go` | Add `RunWaiter` interface |\n| `cmd/cloched/main.go` | Wire `HostRunner` into orchestrator init |\n| `cmd/cloche/init.go` | Create `host.cloche` and `scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` |\n","numLines":249,"startLine":1,"totalLines":249}}}
