{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MmqEt27qjENr55ZAewbyiW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1‚Üí# CLAUDE.md\n     2‚Üí\n     3‚ÜíThis file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n     4‚Üí\n     5‚Üí## Project Overview\n     6‚Üí\n     7‚ÜíCloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\n     8‚Üíenvironments for coding agents, a workflow DSL for linking agentic and script-driven\n     9‚Üítasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n    10‚Üí\n    11‚Üí**Language:** Go\n    12‚Üí\n    13‚Üí**Full design:** `docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n    14‚Üí\n    15‚Üí## Architecture\n    16‚Üí\n    17‚ÜíThree binaries from one Go module:\n    18‚Üí\n    19‚Üí- **`cloche`** (CLI) ‚Äî Short-lived client. Talks to daemon over gRPC. Subcommands: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop`.\n    20‚Üí- **`cloched`** (Daemon) ‚Äî Long-running. Manages container lifecycle, collects status, persists state. Does NOT interpret workflow logic.\n    21‚Üí- **`cloche-agent`** (In-Container) ‚Äî Autonomous. Parses workflow DSL, walks the graph, executes steps, streams status back to daemon. Runs to completion without human intervention.\n    22‚Üí\n    23‚ÜíHexagonal architecture: domain logic is independent of infrastructure. Ports define\n    24‚Üíinterfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, CaptureStore, AgentAdapter). Adapters implement\n    25‚Üíthem (Docker, SQLite, gRPC, Claude Code).\n    26‚Üí\n    27‚Üí```\n    28‚Üícmd/\n    29‚Üí  cloche/           # CLI client\n    30‚Üí  cloched/          # Daemon\n    31‚Üí  cloche-agent/     # In-container entrypoint\n    32‚Üíinternal/\n    33‚Üí  domain/           # Core types (Workflow, Step, Result, Run)\n    34‚Üí  ports/            # Interfaces (store, container, agent, notifier)\n    35‚Üí  adapters/         # Implementations (docker, sqlite, grpc, agents)\n    36‚Üí```\n    37‚Üí\n    38‚Üí## Workflow DSL\n    39‚Üí\n    40‚ÜíSteps report named results; wiring maps results to next steps. `done` and `abort` are\n    41‚Üíbuilt-in terminals. See `docs/workflows.md` for syntax and semantics.\n    42‚Üí\n    43‚Üí## Project Layout\n    44‚Üí\n    45‚ÜíCloche-specific files live in `.cloche/` at the project root:\n    46‚Üí\n    47‚Üí```\n    48‚Üímy-project/\n    49‚Üí‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .cloche/\n    50‚Üí‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ develop.cloche      # Workflow definition\n    51‚Üí‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Dockerfile           # Container image\n    52‚Üí‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ prompts/             # Prompt templates for agent steps\n    53‚Üí‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ overrides/           # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container\n    54‚Üí‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ <run-id>/            # Runtime state (gitignored)\n    55‚Üí‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ src/                     # Existing project source (untouched)\n    56‚Üí‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ CLAUDE.md\n    57‚Üí```\n    58‚Üí\n    59‚Üí## Container Model\n    60‚Üí\n    61‚ÜíOne container per workflow run (not per step). The entire project root is copied into the\n    62‚Üícontainer at `/workspace/`, then override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on\n    63‚Üítop. Results are extracted to git branches. Network is allowlisted.\n    64‚Üí\n    65‚Üí## Agent Support\n    66‚Üí\n    67‚ÜíAgent-agnostic. The `AgentAdapter` interface wraps any coding agent. Initial adapters:\n    68‚ÜíGeneric (arbitrary commands) and Claude Code.\n    69‚Üí"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9be06376-5a43-40f9-8380-030cf073c859","uuid":"3f3a060d-2181-436e-8740-0a18a3760ba4","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/CLAUDE.md","content":"# CLAUDE.md\n\nThis file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n\n## Project Overview\n\nCloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\nenvironments for coding agents, a workflow DSL for linking agentic and script-driven\ntasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n\n**Language:** Go\n\n**Full design:** `docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n\n## Architecture\n\nThree binaries from one Go module:\n\n- **`cloche`** (CLI) ‚Äî Short-lived client. Talks to daemon over gRPC. Subcommands: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop`.\n- **`cloched`** (Daemon) ‚Äî Long-running. Manages container lifecycle, collects status, persists state. Does NOT interpret workflow logic.\n- **`cloche-agent`** (In-Container) ‚Äî Autonomous. Parses workflow DSL, walks the graph, executes steps, streams status back to daemon. Runs to completion without human intervention.\n\nHexagonal architecture: domain logic is independent of infrastructure. Ports define\ninterfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, CaptureStore, AgentAdapter). Adapters implement\nthem (Docker, SQLite, gRPC, Claude Code).\n\n```\ncmd/\n  cloche/           # CLI client\n  cloched/          # Daemon\n  cloche-agent/     # In-container entrypoint\ninternal/\n  domain/           # Core types (Workflow, Step, Result, Run)\n  ports/            # Interfaces (store, container, agent, notifier)\n  adapters/         # Implementations (docker, sqlite, grpc, agents)\n```\n\n## Workflow DSL\n\nSteps report named results; wiring maps results to next steps. `done` and `abort` are\nbuilt-in terminals. See `docs/workflows.md` for syntax and semantics.\n\n## Project Layout\n\nCloche-specific files live in `.cloche/` at the project root:\n\n```\nmy-project/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .cloche/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ develop.cloche      # Workflow definition\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Dockerfile           # Container image\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ prompts/             # Prompt templates for agent steps\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ overrides/           # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ <run-id>/            # Runtime state (gitignored)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ src/                     # Existing project source (untouched)\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ CLAUDE.md\n```\n\n## Container Model\n\nOne container per workflow run (not per step). The entire project root is copied into the\ncontainer at `/workspace/`, then override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on\ntop. Results are extracted to git branches. Network is allowlisted.\n\n## Agent Support\n\nAgent-agnostic. The `AgentAdapter` interface wraps any coding agent. Initial adapters:\nGeneric (arbitrary commands) and Claude Code.\n","numLines":69,"startLine":1,"totalLines":69}}}
